before.enText: of a woman or female animal

data.enText: having a baby or young animal developing inside her/its body

data.chText: 当时我正怀着我们的第三个孩子。
data.enText: I was pregnant with our third child at the time.
a heavily pregnant woman (= one whose baby is nearly ready to be born)

data.chText: 他让女友怀孕了，因此他们即将结婚。
data.enText: He got his girlfriend pregnant and they're getting married.
full of a quality or feeling

data.chText: 她的沉默里充满了批评之意。
data.enText: Her silences were pregnant with criticism.

data.chText: 耐人寻味的停顿；心照不宣的沉默
data.enText: an occasion when nobody speaks, although people are aware that there are feelings or thoughts to express

data.chText: 耐人寻味的停顿；心照不宣的沉默
data.enText: an occasion when nobody speaks, although people are aware that there are feelings or thoughts to express

tr: carrying developing offspring within the body or being about to produce new life

value.def: If a woman or female animal is pregnant, she has a baby or babies developing in her body.

example.ex: Tina was pregnant with their first daughter.
example.tran: 蒂娜怀了他们的第一个女儿。

value.def: A pregnant silence or moment has a special meaning which is not obvious but which people are aware of.

example.ex: There was a long, pregnant silence.
example.tran: 当时出现了长时间耐人寻味的沉默。

example.ex: ...a deceptive peace, pregnant with invisible threats.
example.tran: 一种和平的假象，潜伏着许多无形的威胁

value.tran: 耐人寻味的；意味深长的；心照不宣的
